---
// "Two captains, one slow life." 17:10 wide editorial photo of Clint and
// Dodie (real, from existing site) on the right, narrative on the left.
// Mirrors the Black Tomato "What we do" pattern — but uses the
// opposite direction from ExploreCards above, so the page alternates.
---

<section class="bg-paper text-primary py-24 sm:py-32 lg:py-40 border-t border-rule">
  <div class="max-w-[1400px] mx-auto px-7 lg:px-14">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <p class="font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[0.625rem] font-semibold text-primary/70 mb-5">
          The crew
        </p>
        <h2
          class="font-display font-light leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.025em] text-balance"
          style="font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 3.5vw + 1rem, 2.75rem); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30, 'WONK' 0;"
        >
          Two captains.
          <span class="italic block" style="font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 60, 'WONK' 1;">
            One slow life.
          </span>
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 font-body-lg text-[1.0625rem] leading-[1.7] text-primary/75 text-balance">
          <p>
            Clint runs the boat — USCG Master, RYA Yachtmaster, ten years in
            the chain. He reads weather the way other people read the news.
          </p>
          <p>
            Dodie runs everything else — a galley that produces a different
            cuisine every night, the morning practice on deck if you want it,
            a quiet day if you don't.
          </p>
          <p>
            Fourteen weeks a year, eight cabins each. They do not run hundreds.
            The boat goes where the day-charter crowds don't.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="group inline-flex items-center gap-3 mt-9 font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[0.75rem] font-semibold text-primary border-b-2 border-accent pb-1 hover:text-accent transition-colors"
        >
          Read their story
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="size-3 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M1 8h13M9 3l5 5-5 5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        {/* 4:5 portrait keeps the original photo's framing — switching from
            the 17:10 landscape crop that was cutting Clint and Dodie's
            heads off the top of the image. */}
        <figure class="relative aspect-[4/5] overflow-hidden bg-primary/5">
          <img
            src="/img/source/people/clint-dodie-foredeck-portrait-sunset-01.jpg"
            alt="Clint and Dodie Kendall on the foredeck of their catamaran at sunset"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-[center_top]"
          />
        </figure>
        <figcaption class="font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[0.5625rem] font-semibold text-primary/45 mt-3 text-right">
          Plate 02 · Clint &amp; Dodie · golden hour aboard
        </figcaption>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
